### [1 Kings (1 Samuel) Chapter 28](../../../bib/kjv/sa1028.htm#001.md)

[1 Kings (1 Samuel)](../../../bib/kjv/sa1001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">sa1 28:0</span></span>

Overview

[Sa1 28:1](../../../bib/kjv/sa1028.htm#001.md), Achish puts confidence in
David; [Sa1 28:3](../../../bib/kjv/sa1028.htm#003.md), Saul having
destroyed the witches, [Sa1 28:4](../../../bib/kjv/sa1028.htm#004.md), and
now in his fear forsaken of God, [Sa1
28:7](../../../bib/kjv/sa1028.htm#007.md), has recourse to a witch; [Sa1
28:8](../../../bib/kjv/sa1028.htm#008.md), who, encouraged by Saul, raises
up Samuel; [Sa1 28:15](../../../bib/kjv/sa1028.htm#015.md), Saul hearing
his ruin, faints; [Sa1 28:21](../../../bib/kjv/sa1028.htm#021.md), The
woman and his servants refresh him with meat.

